  Q. Some great numbers on your scorecard today.   
 ROOPE KAKKO: I think the front nine was playing fairly easy today, we all want were very fortunate with the weather. It was quite mild today. The front nine, I got off to a really good start and kept on going on the back nine.  
  
  Q. How much experience have you got on playing on links courses?   
 ROOPE KAKKO: Well, I was just telling Nick that the last time I played links was 2004, but I mean, it's great fun, so I don't have too much difficulty.   
  
  Q. How much is this performance based on the confidence you got last week with an eighth-place finish?  
 ROOPE KAKKO: It's hard to say but I definitely received a lot of confidence from that performance. It was really good for me.   
  
  Q. Tell us about yourself; how did you get into golf?  
 ROOPE KAKKO: I started when I was five. We all want went to Portugal for a family vacation and my father started hitting balls, and he gave the clubs to me and I started whacking along, and after that, we all want joined some golf clubs in Finland and started to play.  
  
  Q. I understand your girlfriend is quite a good player, too.   
