  Q. So you do have a sense?   
 ROOPE KAKKO: Yeah, you just have to land it shorter. Try to play a little softer shots maybe. But the greens were receiving today. We all want got very fortunate because the wind was very mild and just a little drizzle to keep the greens receiving, so I thought after I played a practice round on Tuesday, I thought that it's going to be -- it was blowing and everything was rock hard, but this was very nice.   
  
  Q. Any massive putts?  
 ROOPE KAKKO: On the first, I holed from the fringe. I was short of the green, that must be 15 metres. That's very exciting.   
 I putted great, putted great all the way. I hit a few good putts off the last couple of holes but just didn't hole them. I was putting really well.   
   
